In order to maintain\nefficiency, we employ hyper-reduction via the Energy-Conserving Sampling and\nWeighting approach. We evaluate the proposed coupling approach in the\nreproductive as well as in the predictive regime on a canonical test case that\ninvolves the dynamic propagation of a traveling wave in a nonlinear\nhyper-elastic material.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 22 Oct 2022 20:55:22 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 27 Oct 2022 00:42:30 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 10 Nov 2022 04:58:11 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-11-11"}
